<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Symposium Held to Greet HK's Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 23 (Xinhua) -- At the 100-day countdown of Hong
Kong's return to its motherland, the All-China Youth Federation
held a symposium here today.
</P>
<P>
All the members from the Hong Kong youth delegation, who came
to attend the celebrations, and young people from the various
circles of the Chinese capital attended the symposium.
</P>
<P>
In their speeches, they all expressed their support to the
principles of "one country, two systems" and "Hong Kong people
governing Hong Kong", their expectation of Hong Kong's return and
an early reunification of the motherland, and their wishes to
contribute to the smooth transition, prosperity, and stability of
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Federation also discussed how to enhance the
cooperation between the interior areas and Hong Kong in science,
technology, trade, and so on after 1997.
</P>
<P>
Leading officials from the United Front Work Department of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, and the
Information Office of the State Council attended the symposium.
</P>
<P>
Wang Fengchao, deputy director of the Hong Kong and Macao
Affairs Office of the State Council, and Liu Peng, president of
the All-China Youth Federation, delivered speeches.
</P>
<P>
Wang said he believes that the "one country, two systems"
principle, sponsored by Deng Xiaoping, will surely be carried out in
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region to the letter.
</P>
<P>
Liu voiced his hope that the young generation in China will
seize opportunities going beyond the century, shoulder the
historical responsibilities, and devote themselves to the smooth
transition of Hong Kong as well as its stability and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Delivering speeches at the symposium were the Hong Kong United
Youth Association Chairman Joseph Lee; Vice-Chairmen Kennedy Wong
Ying Ho, Cheung Ming Man, and Eddy S. H. Li; Secretary-general
Alexander Lam Tsan Wing; Founding Chairman Fok Chun Wan; Advisor
Sun Tai Lun, as well as some other officials from the interior
areas.
</P>
<P>
It was also announced that to celebrate Hong Kong's return, the
All-China Youth Federation will hold a large-scale celebration in
Tiananmen Square the evening of June 30th.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
