<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lara Magoni Wins Women's Slalom Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Lara Magoni took her first World
Cup slalom title at the Italian Alpine Championships at Cerreto
Laghi, Italy, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Magoni clocked a winning time of one minute 29.10 seconds to
take the title.
</P>
<P>
Magoni's toughest rival Deborah Compagnoni missed a gate in
the first run and bowed out of the race.
</P>
<P>
Compagnoni, world slalom and giant slalom champion, had led
Magoni for the giant slalom national title on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Morena Gallizio trailed Magoni by 1.01 seconds to finish
second.
</P>
<P>
The men's slalom event is scheduled in Cerreto Laghi on
Tuesday and Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
