<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bayi Rockets Trounces Liaoning Hunters in CBA Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAN, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions Biyi Rockets
trounced Liaoning Hunters 100-68 in the first leg of the finals at
the China's Basketball Association League here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Bayi Rockets, team of the Chinese Army, dominated the match
and surged to a half-time lead of 45-24 at home. In the second
half, the Bayi Rockets further enlarged the gap and wrapped up the
game with a winning margin of 32 points.
</P>
<P>
In the second and final leg of the finals on March 30, the
Liaoning Hunters could only win the title with a winning margin
more than 32 points.
</P>
<P>
In the first leg of the third-place play-off, Guangdong Tigers
beat Shandong Baoyuan 87-69. The 18-point deficit is difficult
for the Shandong team to make up in the second leg which is also
slated for March 30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
