<HEADLINE> Iranian President Meets Saudi Prince </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Ali Akbar
Hashmi Rafsanjani met here today with Saudi Crown Prince Abdollah
Bin Abdul Aziz on the sidelines of the special summit meeting of
the Organization of Islamic Conference (OIC).
</P>
<P>
According to diplomatic sources, the meeting was the first
top-level contact between the two Muslim countries since 1986.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, which lasted about an hour, focused on the
improvement of bilateral relations which got strained following
violent clashes between Saudi security forces and Iranian pilgrims
on the occasion of Haj in 1986, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Iran has recently sent its Foreign Minister Ali Akbar Velayati
to Riyadh to invite Saudi Arabian leaders to attend the upcoming
regular summit meeting of OIC due in Tehran in December this year.
</P>
<P>
The sources said, both Rafsanjani and Abdollah stressed the
need for improving relations of the two important Muslim
countries.
</P>
<P>
The sources quoted the Iranian President as saying that he was
satisfied with the pace of improvement of ties between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Both called for regular official contacts between the two
countries aimed at improving their ties.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that Rafsanjani also attacked unspecified
forces which were bent upon harming relations of Tehran and
Riyadh.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi price observed that good relations between Iran and
his country would have positive impact on the unity of the Muslim
world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
