<HEADLINE> Private Varsity to Be Set Up in Northwestern </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The Board of Management of
the private Lake Secondary School is to construct a university in
Mwanza municipality, northwestern Tanzania, Board Chairman Mahesh
Shah said at Mwanza today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a function in the Lake Secondary School, he said
the university is expected to start in October 1999 with six
departments of art and social science, science, business,
engineering, medicine and health science and law.
</P>
<P>
Shah was quoted by the official Daily News that the university
will be built at Isamilo Hills and will accommodate within the
Lake Secondary School premises.
</P>
<P>
He said the university will do a lot in providing higher
education in order to meet the national demands of highly trained
manpower.
</P>
<P>
The university will also play a big role in assisting the
national plan of meeting the growing demand for graduate
teachers, said the chairman.
</P>
<P>
Shah said the school has enlisted support from donors abroad
to back the project.
</P>
<P>
Currently Tanzania, with a population of about 28 million, has
only three universities --the University of Dar es Salaam, the
Sokoine University of Agriculture in Morogoro and an Open
University. 
</P>
