<HEADLINE> Iraqi Dinar to Appreciate: Central Bank Governor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Governor of the Iraqi Central
Bank Issam Rashid Huweish today said there will be a steady rise
in the purchasing power of the Iraqi dinar this year.
</P>
<P>
In a statement to the Iraqi news agency here, the governor said
that the current year would witness a steady improvement of the
purchasing power of the Iraqi dinar in view of the increase in
commodity supplies and the U.N. permission to import goods and
other materials to meet domestic needs.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the central bank has instructed national
banks to sell and buy foreign currencies, and to bring in
remittances from abroad in accordance with relevant central bank
law and instructions. The move will be done side by side with the
money exchange firms in Baghdad and other governorates.
</P>
<P>
However, the governor did not say how much the dinar will
appreciate in the near future. The exchange rate of the dinar
against the dollar is 1,165:1 today.
</P>
<P>
The prices of foodstuffs have slightly dropped since the
arrival in Iraq of the first consignment of foodstuffs on March
20, although the consignment was rather small in quantity and
diversity.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi citizens have not expressed much joy as the
dispatched foodstuffs are insufficient for the domestic needs and
as they are unaware when a distribution will take place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
