<HEADLINE> Prominent Africans in S. Africa to Form Mediation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Former state leaders and
top government officials from several African countries arrived
here today to form a preventive diplomacy forum of eminent
persons to mediate in political disputes on the continent.
</P>
<P>
The initiative came at a time when Africa is grappling to find
solutions to the crisis in Zaire and the Great Lakes region,
South African Press Association (SAPA) quoted the African Center
for the Constructive Resolution of Disputes (ACCORD)'s statement
as saying.
</P>
<P>
Former President Aristides Perreira of Cape Verde and current
United Nations and Organization of African Unity (OAU) special
representative to the Great Lakes region Ambassador Mohammed
Sahnoun are among those who will serve on the forum.
</P>
<P>
They will be joined by local academics, conflict resolution
practitioners and community leaders like King Makhosonke of
Mpumalanga Province and human rights lawyer Linda Zama, SAPA
said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be chaired by the wife of the late Mozambican
President Samora Machel and close companion of South African
President Nelson Mandela, Graca Machel.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will also be attended by representatives of the
U.N. and OAU, the Southern African Development Community (SADC)
and the inter-governmental authority for development, which
mediates in conflicts in the Horn of Africa.
</P>
<P>
The delegates were scheduled to begin their deliberations at a
private dinner with Mandela in Cape Town, the legislative capital
of South Africa tonight, informed sources said. 
</P>
