<HEADLINE> Cosco Pacific Buys Shares in PRC Ports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Cosco Pacific Ltd today
announced the acquisition of shareholding in four ports in China
from Cosco (HK) Group, which include 50 percent in Qingdao
Terminal, 51 percent in Zhangjiagang Terminal, 10 percent in
Shanghai Terminal and five percent in Yantian Terminal.
</P>
<P>
Sources from BZW Asia Ltd, who acted as financial advisor to
Cosco Pacific, said the price paid by Cosco Pacific is 455 million
HK dollars (58.33 million US dollars), representing a 31 percent
discount to the net asset value of the four stakes. Based on the
1996 net profit of 45.4 million HK dollars (5.82 million US
dollars), price earnings ratio is at 10 times.
</P>
<P>
BZW also acted as underwriter of the 1,199 million HK dollars
(153.72 million US dollars) placing and of Cosco Pacific shares.
</P>
<P>
The placing was priced at 9.95 HK dollars (1.28 US dollars) per
share, representing a five percent discount to the last closing
share price.
</P>
<P>
Chen Zhongbiao, chairman of Cosco Pacific, said: "The
acquisition announced today is on very attractive terms and is
part of our continuing growth strategy to diversify into Asia
Pacific port terminals."  
</P>
