<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey Concerned About Russian-Armenian Arms Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Turkey said today it is concerned
over the illegal arms shipping from Russia to Armenia, saying it
would adversely affect the situation in this region.
</P>
<P>
Turkish Foreign Ministry Deputy Spokesman Sermet Atacanli told
a weekly press briefing here that there had been some illegal
arms shippings between Russia and Armenia in the past two years.
</P>
<P>
He said that Russian Minister for Cooperation with the
Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS) Aman Tuleyev stated on
February 14 that Russia had sold 84 tanks and 50 armored combat
vehicles to Armenia in unlawful ways, and that was confirmed by
Russian Defense Minister Igor Rodionov recently.
</P>
<P>
These incidents have caused much concern from Turkey because
they will bring about a negative impact on peace and stability
in the region, Atacanli added.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Turkish government hoped that the Russian
side would take all necessary measures to prevent similar
occurrences in the future.
</P>
<P>
The Russian authorities concerned has reportedly started an
investigation into the arms deals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
