<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Reclaims More Resources From Waste </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- China retrieved a total of 29
billion yuan (3.63 billion US dollars) worth of waste material
last year, according to the latest statistics.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Ministry of Internal Trade show that
discarded iron and steel and automobiles recycled by the country
has increased over the past few years, so has the reclamation of
waste rubber, plastics, and glass.
</P>
<P>
The research of turning solid waste into usable resources was
listed as state priority during the Eighth Five-Year Plan Period
(1991-1995). Now breakthroughs have been made, especially in
retrieving lead from used batteries. The rate of reclamation
reaches 98 percent.
</P>
<P>
A number of the achievements have been spread across the
country, according to a source in the ministry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
