<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti Crown Prince Leaves Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Crown Prince and
Prime Minister Sheikh Saad Al-Abdullah AL-Salem Al-Sabah left a
London hospital today after a series of medical check-ups, an
official statement here said.
</P>
<P>
The statement released by Kuwaiti Amir Court said that the
crown prince, who has been receiving treatment in London
following a surgery in the colon, will spend some time in the
Al-Sabahiya home outside the British capital for further
recuperation.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Saad went to London on March 10 to continue treatment
after a successful colon operation in Kuwait on March 8.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Saad, who was born in 1930, has been the Kuwaiti prime
minister and Crown Prince since 1978.
</P>
<P>
He is the son of the late Amir Sheikh Abdullah Al-Salem
Al-Sabah, who ruled Kuwait from 1950 to 1965, overseeing the
independence from Britain in 1961. 
</P>
</TEXT>
