<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Improves Ethical Progress in Pilot Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- A total of 100 urban areas and
200 towns and villages have been selected to be pilot zones to
push forward cultural and ethical progress.
</P>
<P>
The namelist was announced by the Propaganda Department of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee at a telephone
conference today.
</P>
<P>
The pilot zones cover all 31 Chinese provinces, municipalities,
and autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
At the end of last year, the central government announced that
300 work units would set an example for other work units in
improving professional ethics.
</P>
<P>
On the basis of improving cultural and ethical progress in
these pilot urban and rural areas, and work units, the overall
quality of China's cities, towns, villages, and work units are
expected to be greatly improved.
</P>
<P>
At the telephone conference, officials of the Propaganda
Department called on local officials to work out detailed and
feasible plans so as to raise the quality of urban residents and
farmers, and enable the people to contribute more to society.
</P>
</TEXT>
