<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Retail Sales Up for January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The value of Hong Kong's total
retail sales in January this year was estimated at 22.1 billion HK
 dollars (2.83 billion US dollars), up 15 percent when compared
with the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
After discounting the effect of price changes over the period,
total retail sales increased by 10 percent in volume, according to
 official statistics released today.
</P>
<P>
Among different types of commodities, sales of motor vehicles
rose most significantly by 71 percent in both value and volume
terms. Sales of valuable goods such as jewellery, watches and
clocks and miscellaneous consumer goods also grew sharply, both by
 17 percent in value.
</P>
<P>
Sales in supermarkets registered increases of 13 percent in
value and six percent in volume. Sales of clothing and footwear
also recorded growth by 14 percent in value and five percent in
volume.
</P>
<P>
Compared with December 1996, total retail sales in January
showed virtually no change in value but increased by two percent
in volume.  
</P>
</TEXT>
