<HEADLINE> Firm Guidance on Chinese as Teaching Medium Proposed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 24 (Xinhua) -- A firm guidance has been
proposed by Hong Kong's Director of Education today for secondary
schools to progressively adopt Chinese as medium of instruction.
</P>
<P>
An official release said schools and sponsoring bodies will be
consulted in April and May before the proposals are finalized.
</P>
<P>
According to research findings, teaching and learning are more
effective if the medium of instruction is the mother tongue.
</P>
<P>
Under the firm guidance, Chinese will be the basic medium of
instruction for all local public sector secondary schools. They
should progressively adopt Chinese as the medium of instruction
for all subjects except English Language and other approved
commercial or technical subjects.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, teaching and learning of the English language in
schools will remain a government priority. Students' English
proficiency will continue to be enhanced.  
</P>
</TEXT>
