<HEADLINE> Closer HK-Guangdong Economic Co-operation Expected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province and Hong
Kong can have much closer economic co-operation in the period
leading to the next century, Chairman of the Hong Kong Trade
Development Council (TDC) Victor Fung said today.
</P>
<P>
Fung said Guangdong and Hong Kong have been close partners for
18 years and the two are economically important to each other.
</P>
<P>
He said there was more scope for co-operation in the areas of
research and development, infrastructural development,
transportation, telecommunications, marketing, property
development and tourism.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that among all the mainland provinces, Guangdong
is the most economically important to Hong Kong. About 80 percent
of Guangdong's exports and imports are conducted through Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1995, Guangdong had utilized over 40 billion US
dollars of Hong Kong investment, accounting for 75 percent of its
cumulative utilized overseas direct investment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
