<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Austrian National Council Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the
Standing Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC),
met with a delegation from the National Council of Austria led by
its president Heinz Fischer.
</P>
<P>
Extending a welcome to Fischer, an old friend of the Chinese
people who is on his fourth visit to China, Qiao recalled his
visit to Austria in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said he is convinced that Fischer's current visit is bound
to enhance his understandings about China, push forward the
cooperation between the two parliaments, and promote the
development of Sino-Austrian friendship.
</P>
<P>
Noting that China and Austria are two friendly nations without
any direct conflicts of interest, Qiao said that China has always
paid much attention to the development of long-term and stable
friendship and cooperation with Austria.
</P>
<P>
During the past few years, he said, with concerted efforts from
both sides, bilateral exchanges and cooperation in politics,
economy, trade, science, technology, culture and education have
been continuously expanding, and the friendship and mutual
understanding between the two peoples has gradually deepened.
</P>
<P>
Qiao went on to say that the constant contacts between leaders
of the two sides have created favorable conditions for the overall
development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Fischer said that China has scored great achievements in its
reform and opening up drive, as well as in its economic
development, and China is playing an increasingly important role
in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
He said he hoped to further strengthen cooperation between the
two parliaments.
</P>
<P>
At Fischer's request, Qiao talked about the achievements and
experience in China's reform and opening up drive, the coordinated
development of China's regional economies, and the role of the
people's congress in China's political system, as well as the
construction of China's socialist democracy and legal system.
</P>
<P>
Qiao also expressed his views on international situations and
explained China's foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
The Austrian delegation arrived here earlier today on an
official good-will visit to China at the invitation of the NPC
Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Chairman of the NPC Standing Committee Chen Muhua held
talks with Fischer this afternoon. 
</P>
