<HEADLINE> CITIC's Assets Approach 200 Billion Yuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The gross assets of the China
International Trust and Investment Corporation (CITIC), had
reached 191.5 billion RMB yuan by the end of the last year, or
14.9 percent more than that of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The net assets of the CITIC, one of China's largest businesses,
amounted to 21.3 billion RMB yuan by the end of 1996, a rise of 25
percent over 1995, according to a recent meeting of CITIC Board of
Directors.
</P>
<P>
The company also achieved 2.474 billion RMB yuan in profit last
year, 21 percent more than the figure for the previous year.
</P>
<P>
It was learned that Zhang Xiao, former president of Industrial
and Commercial Bank of China, has been appointed vice-chairman of
the CITIC in accordance with a State Council decision. 
</P>
