<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Get 500 Million US Dollar Standby Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's central bank, Bank
Indonesia, on Tuesday will sign an agreement with 40 foreign banks
for a standby loan worth 500 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The loan, along with 2 billion US dollars in existing standby
loans, aims to strengthen the country's foreign exchange reserves,
Bank Indonesia Governor Soedradjad Djiwandono said here today.
</P>
<P>
The banks, which arranged the loans, include Germany's
Commerzbank, Japan's Fuji bank, Industrial Bank of Japan and JP
Morgan, Djiwandono said.
</P>
<P>
He said Indonesia in May last year signed a similar agreement
for another 500 million US dollar standby loan.
</P>
<P>
Standby loans are generally good for eight years.  
</P>
