<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Explosion Rocks Bank in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 24 (Xinhua) -- A strong explosion rocked a branch
office of the Dresdner Bank in western Germany early this morning,
causing extensive property damage. But there were no immediate
reports of injury.
</P>
<P>
Police investigating the case in Hattingen, in the North-Rhine
Westfalia state, ruled out the possibility that the Dresdner Bank
might be targeted because it, along with another large German
commercial bank, the Deutsche Bank, had participated in a
controversial takeover attempt by the German steel concern
Krupp-Hoesch against its larger rival Thyssen.
</P>
<P>
Two robbers, who were seen running from the scene after the
blast, had apparently tried to blow up a night safe. But they
failed to shift the protective steel mesh inside the safe, police
said.
</P>
<P>
The blast smashed windows, damaged the facade of the bank
building and destroyed the door and a bulletproof window of a
Deutsche Bank branch office on the other side of the street.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
