<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam Stresses HIV/AIDS Prevention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 24 (xinhua) -- The Vietnamese government will
provide 55 billion dong (about 5 million U.S. dollars) for
HIV-AIDS prevention this year, says an official report released
here today.
</P>
<P>
Eighty percent of the money will be used for grassroots
activities, including experimentation, in fighting the disease and
social evils in 3,000 target communes.
</P>
<P>
More than 33,000 officials from national AIDS prevention
centers have organized prevention programs to raise public
awareness of HIV/AIDS.
</P>
<P>
The programs will provide an estimated 3.4 million people with
basic information about the disease. Education programs will
target 11,000 female prostitutes and 8,742 drug-addicts, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
A total of 5,368 HIV carriers, including 62 foreigners, had
been detected in Vietnam by March 20. AIDS patients in the country
totaled 736. Two-thirds of those affected were drug users.
</P>
</TEXT>
