<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Procurator Confers with His Russian Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Siqing, Procurator-general
of the Supreme People's Procuratorate of China held talks here
today with his Russian counterpart Yuri Skuratov.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that Skuratov's China visit, part of the solid trend
of developing bilateral relations, will be of great importance to
enhancing the friendship and cooperation between the procuratorial
organs of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
There exists a wide range of exchanges and cooperation between
the two procuratorial organs, Zhang said, adding that China and
Russia can exchange procuratorial staff to conduct professional
inspections of each other's countries, and cooperate on educating
and training the personnel.
</P>
<P>
Zhang also briefed the guests on the lawful supervision rights
mandated by the Chinese Procuratorial organs in accordance with
the state criminal law, civil law and administrative procedure law.
</P>
<P>
Skuratov noted that his visit is not only beneficial to
strengthening contact between the two procuratorial organs but
also to improving friendly cooperative ties between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Skuratov is pleased to see China's achievement in building up
the economy and strengthening the legal system.
</P>
<P>
The host and guest exchanged views on implementation of the
treaty on aid in civil and criminal justice between China and
Russia and the upcoming signing of a cooperative agreement between
the two procuratorial organs.
</P>
<P>
Skuratov and his party arrived here on Saturday as guests of
Zhang.  
</P>
</TEXT>
