<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China City to Build Dinosaur Museum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- A museum exhibiting various kinds
of dinosaurs will appear in Changzhou, a city in east China's
Jiangsu province.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Geology and Mineral Resources has signed the
contract with the Changzhou municipal government to build the
China Dinosaur Museum in the new area of the city.
</P>
<P>
The museum will cover 5,000 square meters, with four exhibition
halls, including a prelude hall (exhibiting a scene of Triassic
Period), two halls to exhibit first and last scenes of the
Mesozoic Period, and a reserved hall.
</P>
<P>
Each hall will use multi-media to exhibit geological specimens,
dinosaur fossils, primitive bird fossils, and present vivid scenes
of how dinosaurs lived.
</P>
<P>
Song Ruixiang, minister of Geology and Mineral Resources, said
that the dinosaur museum will help bring science to the people and
increase the people's understanding of the universe.  
</P>
</TEXT>
