<HEADLINE> Guangdong Regulates Project Supervision System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 24 (Xinhua)-- In public biddings of major
construction projects in south China's Guangdong province in 1996,
all projects have invited tenders.
</P>
<P>
Since the introduction of the construction supervision system into
the market in 1985, the cities and counties in Guangdong have set up
supervision stations of construction quality and pricing to
provide scientific methods for ensuring construction quality and
controlling cost overruns.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong now has 164 supervision companies supervising 2,528
projects, with a total investment of 10.71 million yuan (about
1.275 million US dollars). Statistics have shown that in the 3,033
bidding projects in the province last year, 79.5 percent invited
tenders, up 65.9 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Last year, eight projects of Guangdong won the Construction
Award named after Luban, a famous ancient Chinese carpenter and
architect. 
</P>
</TEXT>
