<HEADLINE> Some 200 kg of Heroin Seized in Guangxi, Yunnan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Frontier troops in south China's
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region and southwestern Yunnan Province
seized 218 kg of heroin and more than 30 kg of opium from January
to March 17 this year.
</P>
<P>
The frontier troops also captured 246 alleged narcotics
traffickers who were involved in 189 cases, according to sources
with the Ministry of Public Security.
</P>
<P>
Officials with the ministry said that there was a resurgence of
drug-trafficking in such border areas from the beginning of this
year, and that Chinese frontier troops have made careful plans and
intensified cooperations with troops in neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
On March 5, 12 and 13, frontier troops in Yunnan seized a total
of 63 kg of heroin carried in vehicles, and arrested seven
suspected drug traffickers. 
</P>
