<HEADLINE> McRae Takes Lead in Portugal Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, March 24 (Xinhua) -- World rally championship leader
Colin McRae of Britain took the lead in the Rally of Portugal
after the fourth stage on Monday in Figueira Da Foz.
</P>
<P>
The Subaru driver had led the event after the opening spectator
stage on Sunday but the results were declared null due to a damage
sustained to Finn Tommi Makinen's Mitsubishi brakes.
</P>
<P>
The problem, most likely caused when the car was weighed, meant
that Makinen was unable to put in a competitive time and was 12
seconds slower than McRae. Mitsubishi successfully appealed for
the stage results to be cancelled out.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Sainz of Spain also criticised the opening day's stage,
which was shortened from 3.7 kilometers to 1.5 because of
spectator problems. The Ford driver finished third at the end of
the fourth stage, seven second adrift of McRae.
</P>
<P>
However, the Spaniard announced to pull out of the fifth stage
due to gearbox trouble. 
</P>
