<HEADLINE> Share Prices Up Sharply on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Share prices increased sharply
on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials
Index rose by 29.77 points to close at 2094.25 points today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume was thin at 138.27 million units, worth
339.47 million Singapore dollars (about 239.06 million US
dollars). Advances overtook declines by 167 to 134, while 306
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Labroy was the most actively traded stock as it posted a
turnover of 14.32 million units. It was followed by Sel Dredg
which had 6.29 million of its shares traded. Ber Group was next
with 5.15 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 and the Development Bank of Singapore (DBS) Foreign
shared the top spot on the gainers' list as each of them rose by
60 cents to finish at 14.6 and 17.9 Singapore dollars
respectively. Local car dealer Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C) gained 50
cents to end at 15.2 Singapore dollars, while the City
Developments and the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign
increased by 40 cents each to close at 13.1 and 26.4 Singapore
dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign was the
biggest loser as it declined by 30 cents to end at 15.2 Singapore
dollars. GE Life and the Indonesia Development Fund lost 20 cents
each to 21.2 and 8.6 dollars respectively, while the Keppel
Corporation Hs warrant97 was 18 cents lower at 0.85 Singapore
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970324.0081 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hang Seng China Enterprises Index Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Hang Seng China Enterprises
Index today rose 23.25 points to close at 979.46.
</P>
<P>
The Index, introduced in August 1995, tracks the overall
performance of China's 25 state enterprises listed on the Hong
Kong Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, today's Hang Seng MidCap 50 Index rose 29.76 points
from the previous session to close at 1,806.59.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng MidCap 50 Index comprises 50 most actively-traded
stocks of middle capitalization companies on the local bourse to
help investors and fund managers diversify their portfolios.
</P>
<P>
The two segmented Hang Seng indices are devised by Hang Seng
Index (HSI) Services Limited, a wholly-owned subsidiary of Hang
Seng Bank. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970324.0082 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambique Prepares for Nationwide Census </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The Mozambican government today
began its preparations for the country's second nationwide census,
Carlos Macoo, chief of the Central Population Census Office,
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Heading counting family by family would be employed to conduct
the investigation, said Macoo, explaining that this is the best
method to reflect the sheer facts concerning population and
housing which are most needed for the government's policy-making.
</P>
<P>
So far about 13.6 million U.S. Dollars have been raised for
conducting the project, he said.
</P>
<P>
Among the fund, about three million U.S. Dollars were provided
by the Mozambique government while the rest by the Netherlands,
Denmark, Sweden, the United States and several agencies of the
United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Several sub-committees have been established for training a
total of 52,000 census conductors who would be mainly
college lecturers and students, high school teachers and senior
technicians.
</P>
<P>
The first census was conducted in Mozambique in 1980 when the
country enjoyed a population of 12 million. Mozambique's
population is currently estimated at 17 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
