<DOCNO> XIE19970324.0083 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-24 12:39 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iraq Offers Information About 300 Missing in Gulf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Iraq has declared that it has
provided an international committee in charge of searching for the
missing in the Gulf War with information about 300 missing persons
since the Gulf War in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Iraqi official newspaper Al Jomhoria today quoted an official
source in the Iraqi national committee for searching missing
persons as saying that Iraq has offered information about 300 of
600 missing persons claimed by Saudi Arabia and Kuwait in the
Gulf War.
</P>
<P>
The tripartite international committee is composed of
representatives from the United States, Britain and France.
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi national committee has begun to print some
photographs with names and nationalities of the other missing
persons and put them in public places all over the country so that
every citizen can recognize them and give information directly to
the government, the source said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
