<DOCNO> XIE19970324.0084 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-Russian Trade Develops Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 24 (Xinhua) - Russian-China trade is expected to
reach seven or eight billion U.S. dollars in volume in 1997,
following a steady growth in recent years.
</P>
<P>
China became the fifth largest trade partner of Russia's in
1996, after Ukraine, Germany, the United States and Belorussia,
the Itar-TASS News Agency quoted the Russian Foreign Trade
Ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
Russia's trade with China accounted for 4.5 percent of its
total foreign trade volume in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said Russia is interested in participating in
China's Three Gorges Project and plans to provide a loan for the
hydro power station.
</P>
<P>
Russia also plans to help China build a factory to produce
enriched uranium for nuclear power stations and is interested in
launching joint ventures in China to produce combines and maintain
Russian-made civil aircraft. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
