<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 80 to 100 Tamil Rebels Killed, 50 to 70 Injured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 24 (Xinhua) -- At least 80 to 100 Tamil rebels
were killed and 50 to 70 others wounded by Sri Lankan Naval
Patrols today in Northern Province of the country, according to a
military spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that a group of 8 Tamil rebels' boats were
sighted by Naval Patrols who intercepted and engaged them in the
east of Mullaitivu, Northern Province.
</P>
<P>
Subsequently 5 rebel groups each consisting of 5 boats,
including boats fitted with explosives for suicide missions,
joined the confrontation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Fighting continued for about two hours in the morning. 10 rebel
boats were heavily damaged. He said that the Navy believed at
least 80 to 100 rebels were killed and 50 to 70 wounded during the
confrontation, while the Navy suffered one sailor killed and 8
others wounded in the action. Two Naval craft were slightly
damaged due to rebel gun fire, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 14-year-old war for a
separate Tamil state in the north and east of the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
