<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed
higher today as the market awaits news on a possible rate-hike in
the States.
</P>
<P>
It ended at 78.68 US cents from 78.40 at Friday's close and
traded between 78.61 and 78.75 on the day.
</P>
<P>
A foreign exchange dealer said the local market was holding
short positions ahead of the long-awaited meeting concerning the
Federal Reserve's monetary policy.
</P>
<P>
This is because a rise in US official rates will reduce their
margin to Australian rates, making local securities less
attractive to global investors.
</P>
<P>
He forecast the local currency would fall below 78 US cents in
the short term, if a rate cut eventuated.
</P>
<P>
On the cross-rate, the Australian dollar was mixed, it ended at
96.74 from 96.84 against the Japanese yen, and at 1.3292 from
1.3235 against the Deutsche marks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
