<DOCNO> XIE19970324.0097 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Encourages Light Industrial Giant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- China will encourage more mergers
and acquisition in its light industrial sector, hoping to form 100
conglomerates with annual sales volume of more than two billion
yuan by the turn of the century.
</P>
<P>
"Such redistribution of assets allows the companies to expand
at a low cost and will help to increase their competitiveness
greatly," said an official with the General Association of Light
Industry.
</P>
<P>
The government will also grant financial support to industry
leaders in the sector, for mergers of poorly-performing
enterprises and technical upgrading.
</P>
<P>
Firms of a certain size will be authorized to open non-banking
institutions and financial companies of their own, and will raise
funds by floating corporate bonds and stocks.
</P>
<P>
They will also receive more freedom for exports to promote
their product image in the international market and build up their
own strength.
</P>
<P>
China's light industry rose at a stable rate last year, with
the export of its products keeping relatively high growth.
</P>
<P>
Industrial leaders have emerged in the sector, dominating the
market as their strength increases. Producers of refrigerators,
freezers, washing machines and air conditioners already have
increased their market share to 93 percent, 88 percent, 83 percent
and 58 percent, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
