<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Retail of Consumer Goods Grows in Shanghai in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Recent data show that retail of
consumer goods in Shanghai has kept growing in the past two
months, hitting 11 billion yuan in total value in February, up
five percent from February 1996.
</P>
<P>
Official sources say that the actual growth of the sales volume
of retailed consumer goods was 4.1 percent, if the factors of
inflation were excluded.
</P>
<P>
All Chinese people celebrated their traditional Spring Festival
and the Lantern Festival in February this year, which continued
the brisk purchasing of Shanghai people from the beginning of this
year, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Major department stores, including those in Huangpu District
and Nanjing Street, in Shanghai, also grabbed the chance to sell
their wares through numerous promotion activities.
</P>
<P>
The sales volume of consumer goods for daily use surge 5.1
percent in February from the same period of last year, topping
4.35 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the sale of color TV sets in 16 major department
stores increased by more than 30 percent, with the sale of video
compact disc machines 11 times that in last February.
</P>
<P>
A sharp growth of gold ornaments was also seen in February
because of a price cut. The combined monthly sales volume of two
major stores of gold products rose by 23.2 percent, to 84.8
million yuan last month.
</P>
<P>
Brisk sales of consumer goods also took place in the suburban
Shanghai, that saw a growth rate of retailed consumer goods above
the city's average last month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
