<HEADLINE> China First Participating In World Environmental Awareness Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 24 (Xinhua) -- China has been invited to take
part in a worldwide environmental survey to gain a better
understanding of the sense of environmental awareness among the
Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
The survey, sponsored by a Canadian environmental-monitoring
corporation, is held annually to reach an international consensus
on environmental protection. This year's survey will be the
biggest in the project's history, with 24 countries taking part in
the activity to be held later this month.
</P>
<P>
The Guangzhou Damen Information Industrial Company Ltd, will
conduct the survey, which covers nine cities, including Beijing,
Shanghai, Guangzhou, Shenyang, Chengdu, Hangzhou and Shenzhen.
</P>
