<HEADLINE> Australian Shares Jump </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Bank shares ignited the
Australian share market today as investors rushed for the
top-yielding stocks in anticipation of big bank mergers.
</P>
<P>
Traders said bank shares rallied as investors waited for the
release of the Wallis report which could be handed down at any
time.
</P>
<P>
The leading market indicator, the all ordinaries index, drew
strength from rising bank stocks to finish 15.7 points higher at
2402.1.
</P>
<P>
News that the country's largest bank, the National Australia
Bank Ltd, would buyback 89.25 million shares on the market from
April 8 was seen as a sign the bank could be preparing for a major
acquisition post-Wallis.
</P>
<P>
Commonwealth Bank shares jumped 32 cents higher, Westpac added
21 cents and ANZ was 18 cents firmer today.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index increased 36.4 points to 3755.3,
while the all resources index slipped 1.6 points to 1361.9.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 241.82 million shares valued at
648.77 million Australian dollars (509.28 million US dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
