<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Maintenance-Free Battery Plant Launched in Pudong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The first plant in China to
produce maintenance-free car batteries has been launched in
Pudong, Shanghai, the country's trade and financial hub.
</P>
<P>
The plant was jointly set up by the American Delphi Automotive
Systems, and the Shanghai Electronics Company. The two partners
poured 55 million US dollars in total investment in the project.
</P>
<P>
Delphi officials said that the plant is the biggest project in
China that Delphi Automotive System has been involved in. The
companies had set up 11 joint ventures in China previously.
</P>
<P>
Production is to start early next year. The plant expects to
output one million batteries by the the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Some anti-pollution devices will be installed in the plant to
keep water, air, and noise pollution to a minimum.
</P>
<P>
Industrial sources noted that there is a lot to be tapped in
Shanghai's market of auto-parts, since automobile industry is a
one of the pillar sectors of the municipality's economy.
</P>
<P>
Delphi Automotive Systems is one of the leading suppliers in
the world of automobile components, and their products had a total
sale volume of 27.8 billion dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Electronics Company, China's biggest manufacturer of
electronics products and machinery, sold a total of six billion
dollars-worth products last year.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese company also has spent 1.8 billion US dollars to
buy advanced technology and equipment from abroad over the past
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
