<HEADLINE> HK Signs Air Services Agreement with Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong and Thailand
governments today signed an air services agreement, an official
announcement said today.
</P>
<P>
A Hong Kong government spokesman said the agreement would
provide the necessary legal framework to ensure Hong Kong's air
links with Thailand would continue smoothly after June 30, 1997.
</P>
<P>
He said the Thailand market was important for Hong Kong's
Cathay Pacific and Dragonair. Cathay Pacific currently operates 35
services per week to Bangkok and Dragonair three services per week
to Phuket. Both airlines together carried a total of some 0.9
million passengers in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The Thai Airways operates 46 services per week to Hong Kong,
carrying some 1.04 million passengers in 1996. 
</P>
