<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Stock Market Remains at High Level in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stock market turnover
remained at a high level in February after a month of heavy
trading in January, according to the Hong Kong Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
Average daily turnover for the 18 trading days in February was
8.698 billion HK dollars (1.12 billion US dollars), a decrease of
22 percent as compared with the previous month.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover value of the month was 156.56 billion HK dollars
(20.2 billion US dollars) compared with 246.158 billion HK dollars
(31.55 billion US dollars) in January.
</P>
<P>
A total of 73 billion shares changed hands in February, as
against 116.098 billion in January. The average turnover by
volume was 4.056 billion shares, down 23 percent from January.
</P>
<P>
Average daily turnover for the first two months of the year was
10.068 billion HK dollars (1.29 billion US dollars), compared with
6.726 billion HK dollars (862.3 million US dollars) in the same
period.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover by value was 402.718 billion HK dollars (52
billion US dollars) during the first two months of the year,
compared with 269.044 billion HK dollars (34.71 billion US
dollars) for the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index at the end of February was 13,398.72, a
rise of one percent from last month and 20 percent from February
1996.
</P>
<P>
The market capitalization at the end of February this year was
3,564.92 billion HK dollars (459.98 billion US dollars), an
increase of 33 percent over the corresponding period in 1996.
</P>
</TEXT>
