<HEADLINE> Bean Inoculation Recommended </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- A Ugandan scientist recommended
bean inoculation to boost growth and increase production of soyabenas
in the field, the New Vision reported today.
</P>
<P>
Martin Wamaniala, a sicentist working with Agribusiness
Development Center of Uganda, said that soyabean crop responds
positively to application of inoculation prior to planting.
</P>
<P>
The recommended inoculant is rhizobium produced by the
Department of Soil Science and Kakira Oil Mill's laboratory in
Makerere University here.
</P>
<P>
Inoculation of the seeds for planting should be done on the
planting day and if the planting is not done then the seeds should be
inoculated again before planting to secure the seeds are properly
inoculated.
</P>
<P>
Ten kilogram of seed should be mixed with a liter of water to
which one tea spoon of sugar is added to assist the rhizobium to
stick to the seeds. enditem

