<HEADLINE> Rafsanjani Calls U.S., Israel Worst Enemies of Muslims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani described here today the United States and Israel as
the worst enemies of Muslim countries.
</P>
<P>
"At the present time, America and Israel are leading the
hostility towards Muslims," Rafsanjani said when answering a
question at a news conference here.
</P>
<P>
He urged the Muslim countries to enhance their solidarity to
scuttle the conspiracies hatched by imperialist forces to
subjugate Islamic nations.
</P>
<P>
Iran opposes the U.S.-sponsored peace process in Middle East,
he said, there had been chances of revival of violence since the
launching of Washington's initiative.
</P>
<P>
The attitude of the United States towards the U.N. resolutions
condemning the Israeli plans for Jewish settlement had exposed its
real face to the Arab world, Rafsanjani said when responding to
another question.
</P>
<P>
"To me, the face of (U.S. President) Mr. Clinton sitting on a
wheel chair with a broken leg vetoing the resolutions on Palestine
twice within one week is very much similar to the face of (former
Israeli Foreign Minister) Moshe Dayan sitting on a tank shooting
the Palestinian people," he said.
</P>
<P>
"If there is any reward to be given to the world's top
extremist, (Israeli President Benjamin) Mr. Natanyahu should be
nominated for it," he said.
</P>
<P>
The reason was that the hardline shown by Natanyahu has
definitely called Muslims' awakening, he said.
</P>
<P>
"It should be understood that occasionally extremist move on
the other side also could help the Islamic world," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian President also expressed concern over the
"inappropriate" response of the Muslim world towards Israel's
adamant approach to building a Jewish settlement in Jerusalem, and
the U.S. veto on the Security Council resolutions condemning
Israeli moves.  
</P>
</TEXT>
