<HEADLINE> Israel Rejected to Participate in Oman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The Sultanate of Oman has
rejected Israel's application for participating in an
international fair it hosts in October in view of the stalemated
Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Al Ettehad, a United Arab Emirates daily, today quoted Ali Saed
Alhaeg, general director of the Omani company of the fair and the
international trade, as confirming that the Omani authorities
turned down Israel's application in the 4th Muscat event.
</P>
<P>
As for the reasons for the refusal, the official said that the
stumbling of peace process in the Middle East was one of the
reasons.
</P>
<P>
All Arab states will participate in the fair so Oman decided
not to accept the Israeli request, he added.
</P>
<P>
Israel established economic relations with Oman last
May. However, the Omani government declared to stop all trade ties
with Israel at the meeting of Declaration of Damascus held last
December in Cairo, Egypt. 
</P>
