<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Egyptian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Egyptian newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Al-Ahram:
</P>
<P>
-- Israel's construction of 6,500 units in Har Homa
neighborhood in East Jerusalem is part of its attempt to isolate
the city from other parts of the West Bank, Palestinian leader
Yasser Arafat said in his speech before the inaugural session of
the OIC extraordinary summit.
</P>
<P>
Al Akhbar:
</P>
<P>
-- Israeli Authorities Sunday permitted 280 physicians from
the West Bank and Gaza Strip to enter Israel and to move between the
two areas, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Al-Gomhuria:
</P>
<P>
-- Two Palestinians were wounded near Bethlehem when
Israeli soldiers opened fire at them Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Gazette:
</P>
<P>
-- The Arab League Sunday reiterated the Arab's support for the
Middle East peace process as a strategic option and said that the
United States vetos in the U.N. Security Council encourage Israel
to pursue its illegal settlement policy. 
</P>
