<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PKK Rebels Kill Four People in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Rebels of the outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK) attacked a village in Hatay Province
bordering Syria and killed four Turks at the weekend, an official
statement said today.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of the Hatay Province said
that a group of PKK militants Sunday evening raided peasants
working in the fields of the Yoncaduzu village of Erzin town and
shot dead four, including one soldier of the Turkish security
forces on duty.
</P>
<P>
Two village guards were also slightly wounded in the attack,
the statement added.
</P>
<P>
Hatay province is one of the hot places where the PKK stages
attacks against the military and civilian targets to gain autonomy
from the Turkish government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
