<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Expands GSM Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The fourth phase of expansion of
the digital mobile telephone network has begun in the Beijing
municipality.
</P>
<P>
The expansion of the Beijing Telecommunication's GSM network
(global service for mobile communication) will use Nokia's
advanced technology.
</P>
<P>
Upon completion, the municipality will double its wireless
telecommunication switching capacity to 500,000 handsets.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Telecommunication's GSM network, first launched in
April 1995, now has a capacity of 250,000 handsets with more than
200,000 subscribers.
</P>
<P>
Over the past two years, Beijing has expanded the mobile
telecommunications network three times.
</P>
<P>
China's telecommunication GSM network has been linked with more
than 250 prefectures and 1,170 counties across the country and
opened roaming function in several countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this year, the country will offer the GSM service
in 300 prefectures and 1,400 counties, according to a national
plan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
