<HEADLINE> Manila Hopes to Enhance Military Contacts With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Undersecretary of
Defense Feliciano Gacis today expressed the hope that military
contacts will be further enhanced in the future between the armed
forces of the Philippines and China.
</P>
<P>
Gacis was holding talks with Vice Admiral Yang Yushu, commander
of the East China Sea Fleet of the Chinese navy.
</P>
<P>
Yang arrived here Sunday with two Chinese Navy ships under his
command on a three-day goodwill visit, the first to the country by
the Chinese Navy ships.
</P>
<P>
Describing the visit as "historic", Gacis said he believed the
visit will further deepen mutual understanding between the two
country's armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Yang also held separate talks with Rodolfo Garcia, deputy chief
of staff of the Philippine Armed Forces, and Eduardo Santos,
commander of the Philippine Navy.
</P>
<P>
Manila is the last stop of the three-nation Southeast Asia tour
by the two Chinese ships, one missile destroyer and one missile
frigate, which have already visited Thailand and Malaysia.
</P>
</TEXT>
