<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Donates to Quake Victims in Iran, Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia today donated
50,000 US dollars each to the governments of Iran and Pakistan to
help in the rehabilitation of areas and victims affected by the
recent earthquakes in the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi today
presented the cheques to Iranian ambassador to Malaysia Hossein
Feraydoun and the Pakistani High Commission's first secretary
Zehra Akbari respectively in a simple ceremony at the foreign
ministry here.
</P>
<P>
The minister said on the occasion "we are very saddened by the
disasters which claimed many lives and hope that Malaysia's
assistance will help in some way to rehabilitate the families and
areas concerned."
</P>
<P>
The Ardabil region in northwest Iran was rocked by an
earthquake measuring six on the open-ended Richter scale on
February 28 killing more than 1,000 people and rendering tens of
thousands more homeless.
</P>
<P>
The quake in Pakistan's southwestern Baluchistan province a
day earlier killed at least 48 people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
