<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 08:30 GMT, March 24 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN DIEGO, March 23 (Xinhua) - A Chinese vice admiral said here
today that the first visit to the continental United States by
three Chinese Warships has opened a new chapter in the annuals of
relations between the two navies.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yongguo, commander of the Chinese navy South China Sea
Fleet, said that the visit has deepened mutual understanding and
enhanced bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh
Chok Tong left here today for Vientiane on a two-day official
visit to Laos, the first by a Singapore prime minister to the
country, the Prime Minister's Office announced today.
</P>
<P>
SEOUL, March 24 (Xinhua) -- At least 13 people were killed and
some 20 others injured when a train and a bus collided at a
railway crossing in South Korea early today.
</P>
<P>
The train struck the rear of the bus carrying up to 50 people,
which was driving over the tracks at the crossing at Namwon in the
southwest of the country, according to police sources.
</P>
<P>
The train was heading for Seoul from Sunchon when the accident
occurred at about 9.00 a.m. (local time).
</P>
<P>
DHAKA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The main opposition Bangladesh
Nationalist Party (BNP) will hold a public meeting here today to
protest the attack and arrest of party workers and leaders
occurred on Sunday's nationwide strike.
</P>
<P>
The eight-hour strike enforced by the BNP was marked by
sporadic violence that left more than 200 injured including former
 Home Minister Matin Chowdhury. At least 150 persons were arrested
 in Dhaka on charge of damaging vehicles and disrupting normal
life.
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The Extraordinary Summit of the
 Organization of Islamic Conference (OIC) has adopted a 25-point
"Islamabad Declaration" to broaden cooperation among OIC members
states in all spheres.
</P>
<P>
The declaration was adopted here on Sunday night at the end of
the one-day OIC special summit in commemorating the 50th
anniversary of independence of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The declaration said that comprehensive peace in the Middle
East could not be achieved without the implementation of the UN
Security Council resolutions 242, 338 and 425 as well as the
principles of "land for peace". 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
