<HEADLINE> Cambodian Acting Head of State Meets Chinese Guest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The acting head of State of
Cambodia and the President of its National Assembly, Chea Cim,
today met with Chinese State Councillor and Secretary-General of
the State Council Luo Gan and congratulated him on his successful
visit.
</P>
<P>
Cim said Luo's visit would further develop Cambodian-Chinese
friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said Cambodia will hold local elections this year and
general elections next year. Cambodia will continue to make
efforts to maintain peace and political stability which is the
prerequisite for economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Luo highly praised the good relations between China and
Cambodia and said China will develop its friendly, cooperative
relations with Cambodia in an all-round way on the basis of the
five principles of peaceful coexistence.
</P>
<P>
Luo said the Chinese government and people will continue to
support Cambodia in its efforts to maintain its national stability
and develop its economy.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed Cim on the Chinese situation.
</P>
<P>
Luo arrived here Friday from Vietnam for a four-day visit,
which ends this afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
