<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
drifted lower today, largely as a result of a number of leading
stocks going ex-dividend.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 6 points lower at 2,224 with a turnover
of nearly 60 million NZ dollars (41 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom was the most actively traded stock, accounting for 40
percent of the total turnover. The company was the only gainer
among the main leaders, with shares climbing 5 cents to 655 cents.
</P>
<P>
Among the losers, Air New Zealand dropped 5c to 262c, Brierley
Investment fell 2c to 135c, Carter Holt Harvey dipped 3c to 302c,
Fletcher Building lost 3c to 429c and Lion Nathan slided 8c to
322c.
</P>
<P>
Overall, there were 39 rises and 46 falls.  
