<HEADLINE> Manila, MILF Form Ceasefire Monitoring Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government and the
Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) have officially declared the
establishment of a third independent body to monitor the local
ceasefire between them, the Philippine News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The monitoring body which formed on Sunday is composed of the
Philippine Notre Dame University Peace Center, Maguindanao
Province Professional Employees Association, the Protestant
Lawyers League of the Philippines and the local media.
</P>
<P>
The group is required to submit before peace negotiators today
a draft paper on how they would function, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The group's first assignment will be to investigate the March
16 bombing incident inside the MILF's Camp Abubakar in Barira,
Maguindanao, where 11 civilians were allegedly killed by military
bomb attacks.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the government and the MILF peace negotiators are
expected to release a joint press statement regarding other
matters taken up during their two-day closed door meeting that
would end today in Sultan Kudarat, Maguindanao. 
</P>
</TEXT>
