<HEADLINE> 9th Asian Congress of Pediatrics Opens in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The 9th Asian Congress of
Pediatrics officially opened here today with 300 pediatric experts
present to exchange recent progress in pediatric field.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Hong Kong Pediatric Society and the Hong Kong
College of Pediatricians, the Asian Congress of Pediatrics is held
every other year under the auspices of the Asian Pediatric Society
of Southeast Asian Region and the International Pediatric
Association.
</P>
<P>
With the theme of "Pediatric Priorities in the 21st Century",
the congress has received about 700 scientific papers on various
aspects of child health and disease.
</P>
<P>
In his opening speech, Chan Chok-wan, prid that prime priorities will be give
n to the promotion of
child health and the prevention of childhood illnesses.
</P>
<P>
He said emphasis will be placed on holistic care to promote the
physical, psychological and social well-being of infants, children
and adolescents.
</P>
<P>
Topics at the congress will include breast feeding, nutrition,
growth, family-centered care, community child health, student
health and adolescent medicine.  The Congress will end at March
27. 
</P>
