<HEADLINE> Malaysian King Urges People to Make MSC A Success </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian King Tuanku
Ja'afar today called upon the people in the country to make the
Multimedia Super Corridor (MSC) project a success.
</P>
<P>
All the people must make the MSC project a success if they do
not want Malaysia to be left behind in mastering information
technology, the King said when opening the first meeting of the
third term of the ninth Parliament here today.
</P>
<P>
Discussions on the MSC will be given priority with several
cyber bills to be tabled at this session, according to official
sources.
</P>
<P>
The development of the MSC is the Malaysian government's most
important effort this year and a big effort by Malaysia to master
the information field which would shape the future development of
the world.
</P>
<P>
The MSC is a 15 kilometers by 50 kilometers zone stretching
southward from central Kuala Lumpur, which is specially designed
for high-tech projects.
</P>
<P>
The King said "the MSC offers a conducive environment that is
specially designed to facilitate the merging of operators and
companies to reap the benefits of the information age."
</P>
<P>
He said more emphasis should be made on science and technology
so that the country would be more capable of using, adapting and
upgrading imported technology besides developing local technology.
</P>
<P>
"Investments in new technology will give the country a
competitive edge in the field of information technology. To
achieve this, the government will draft the Telecommunication
Master Plan," he said. 
</P>
