<HEADLINE> Ivanisevic Avoids Upset in Lipton Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Fourth seed Goran Ivanisevic
survived a big scare before routing local favourite Vince Spadea
in a protracted third rounder at the Lipton Championships in Key
Biscayne, Florida on Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
After conceding the first set 3-6, the Croatian won the two
succeeding sets to sail further in the tournament 3-6, 7-6 and 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Ivanisevic, runner-up here last year, had a sluggish start and
missed many his groundstrokes.
</P>
<P>
Spadea jumped to a 5-3 lead and served out the first set with
two more aces in the final game.
</P>
<P>
Ivanisevic squandered a set point by netting a backhand before
taking the tiebreaker 7-4.
</P>
<P>
In the decider set, the atmosphere turned ugly when the umpire
overruled two Ivanisevic double-faults in the eighth
game.
</P>
<P>
As Spadea lost his composure the fourth seed took advantage by
breaking Spadea for a 5-4 lead before serving out his own game.
</P>
