<HEADLINE> Singapore PM Visits Laos, Witnesses Signing of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh
Chok Tong left here today for Vientiane on a two-day official
visit to Laos, the first by a Singapore prime minister to the
country, the Prime Minister's Office announced today.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, which is Goh's first trip to the country, the
prime minister will witness the signing of the Singapore-Laos
Investment Guarantee Agreement.
</P>
<P>
Goh is accompanied by senior government officials and about 20
Singapore businessmen on the visit.
</P>
<P>
In Vientiane, Goh will also call Lao President Nouhak
Phoumsavan, and hold talks with Prime Minister Khamtay Siphandone,
the Prime Minister's Office said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
During Goh's stay there, a seminar on investment opportunities
in Laos will hold for the Singapore delegation to brief the
Singapore businessmen on the country's efforts to woo foreign
investors.
</P>
<P>
Though Singapore's investment in Laos is small compared to its
investment in Vietnam and Myanmar, there is growing interest in
the country among Singapore businessmen, local media noted.
</P>
<P>
Singapore is now the 14th largest investor in Laos, with
investments mainly in hotels and infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
Singapore is also one of Laos's largest trading partners, with
total bilateral trade amounting to around 45 million US dollars
last year, according to the Singapore Trade Development Board
figures.
</P>
<P>
Laos is keen on joining the Association of the Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) and many observers expect it to do so later this
year, together with Cambodia and Myanmar, to bring the membership
of the regional group to ten in the year when the ASEAN marks its
30th anniversary.  
</P>
</TEXT>
