<HEADLINE> Thailand Prepares Action Plan to Push Service Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The Thai Commerce Ministry and
the Tourism Authority of Thailand (TAT) are jointly working on an
action plan to spur Thai exports of services as the country is
facing a slowdown in its exports of industrial goods.
</P>
<P>
Medical, catering, entertainment and health-care services could
be among the rising foreign exchange earners in Thailand,
according to the Export Promotion Department of the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The action plan, which is expected to be completed within the
coming two months, will help generate about 4 billion U.S. dollars
from the country's service exports, the department said.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Thailand's competitiveness in textiles, jewelry,
leather, furniture and decorative items is declining and the
department indicated that there is a need to explore the country's
services sector to reinforce its exports, in particular to the
Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
Thai entertainment products like music and movie have a great
potential for export, according to the department.
</P>
<P>
The plan is also aimed at attracting more foreign tourists to
Thailand to enjoy Thai-style services and helping the country
bring down its current account deficits, local newspapers said.
</P>
</TEXT>
