Islands have started work to establish a new business district in
the Thuwunna area in Yangon, The New Light of Myanmar reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The 202-million-US dollar project is jointly undertaken by the
Thuwunna Development Co (Myanmar), Bijoux Holdings Public Co Ltd
(Virgin Islands) and Bijoux Myanmar Corporation (Thailand) with
the cooperation of the Department of Human Settlement and Housing
Development (DHSHD) of the Myanmar Construction Ministry.
</P>
