<HEADLINE> New Fund to Support Scientific Research on Campuses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- China set up a new fund last
week to encourage the scientific and technical creativity of high
school students.
</P>
<P>
Today's "China Daily" quoted sources as saying that the fund of
five million yuan (602,000 US dollars), established by the
All-China Students' Federation, is aimed at helping high school
students turn their creative thoughts into real products.
</P>
<P>
China's high school education has long been
examination-oriented, with the main purpose qualifying students
for college entrance examination.
</P>
<P>
The model is under increasing criticism for leaving little
scope for students' creative thinking and ability to handle daily
life situations, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
A fund evaluation board will select about 400 projects from the
applicants each year and give each of those chosen 2,000 yuan (240
US dollars) to carry out their ideas, according to the
paper. 
