<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Costa Ricans Sink Americans in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rica grabbed a narrow 3-2
victory over the United States on Sunday in the final round of the
CONCACAF World Cup qualifiers, thanks to a 76th minute goal from
striker Ronald Gomez.
</P>
<P>
The victory left Costa Rica alongside Mexico atop the CONCACAF
table, with perfect record of four points out of two games. The
United States also notched four points but from three matches. The
top three teams will advance to the World Cup finals in France.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica, which beat the United States 2-1 at home in the
semifinal round, pressed from the outset and took the lead after
only 10 minutes when Hernan Medford received a cross and beat two
American defenders before slamming home the opener.
</P>
<P>
American forward Eric Wynalda tied it in the 24th, only to see
Mauricio Solis restoring the lead 13 minutes before halftime.
</P>
<P>
The second half saw the Americans back to picture when
substitute Roy Lassiter scored in the 68th by wrongfooting two
defenders at the top of the penalty area and beating Costa Rican
keeper Hermidio Barrantes to the long side.
</P>
<P>
Then came the fatal 76th minute goal with Harold Wallace of
Costa Rica picking up a loose ball outside the penalty area and
chipping a cross to Gomez, who effectively sealed the victory.
</P>
<P>
Canada, Jamaica and El Salvador are the other teams in the
final round of qualifying.
</P>
<P>
In the next round games, the United States will face Mexico on
April 20, while Costa Rica takes on El Salvador on May 4.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
