<HEADLINE> Italian Medical Aid Arrives in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The medical aid provided by the
Italian government to Albania arrived today in Vlora, a southern
town of Albania.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the lot of medicines could be used by
300,000 people for six months.
</P>
<P>
The first materials of the Italian assistance sent to the
country on March 21 was military supplies offered to Albania's
interior ministry.
</P>
<P>
Italy is a neighboring country of Albania. Since the situation
was tense in the Balkan country, Italian officials urged many
times that the European Union should coordinate the policy toward
Albania, and provide humanitarian, financial and other material
aid to the country.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here, Italian Foreign Minister
Lamberto Dini said today that the time was now ripe for
humanitarian aid to Albania, while "getting involved in a military
situation was not opportune".
</P>
<P>
Talking to reporters on the sidelines of a rally in Rome on
Sunday, Dini said Italy has a responsibility to shelter needy
refugees but not "the illegal immigration that is now being
reorganized by crime gangs who put people on boats in exchange for
money".
</P>
<P>
It was reported that there are some 10,000 Albanian refugees
having fled into Italy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
