<HEADLINE> Shanxi Reemploys 96 Percent Laid-off Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 100,000 laid-off workers
in north China's Shanxi province have found new jobs, thanks to
the province's reemployeement program last year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, 85,000 surplus workers in state-owned enterprises
in the province were rearranged.
</P>
<P>
Those figures accounted for 96 percent of the total number of
laid-off workers in the province, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
Shanxi province is a traditional energy and heavy chemical
industrial base in China. In recent years, the province has faced
a tough task of reemployment as a result primarily of industrial
restructuring.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, 1,944 employment consulting agencies
had been set up across the province, which covered 95 percent of
the total population.
</P>
<P>
At present, the province has brought unemployeement rate down
to below 1.5 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
