<HEADLINE> Chinese Shuttlers Bag Home Three Golds in Swiss Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 23 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese shuttlers reapt their
juicy harvest by bagging home three out of five gold medals at
stake in the Swiss Open badminton championships concluded in
Basle, Switzerland on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Dong Jiong, the Olympic runner-up, awarded China the men's
singles crown by nipping Olympic champion Poul-Erik Hoyer-Larsen
of Denmark in straight sets 17-14, 15-11.
</P>
<P>
Ye Zhaoying squandered her first set win by losing the latter
two in an identical score of 11-6, surrendering the women's
singles final to European champion Camilla Martin of Denmark 9-12,
11-6, 11-6.
</P>
<P>
The other two gold medals for China were from the women's
doubles and the mixed doubles.
</P>
<P>
Ge Fei and Gu Jun, the number one women's pair in the world,
won an all-Chinese final by beating Han Jingna and Ye Zhaoying
9-12, 15-2, 15-11.
</P>
<P>
Ge Fei won her second gold again by pairing with Li Yong in the
mixed doubles and routing their Indonesian opponents Flandy
Limpele and Minarti Timur 15-9, 15-9.
</P>
<P>
The men's doubles title went to South Korea when Lee Dong-soo
and Yoo Yong-sung bt Sigit Budiarto and Chandra Wijaya of
Indonesia 9-15, 15-11, 15-4. 
</P>
