<HEADLINE> North China Province to Use More Foreign Funds in Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, March 24 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei province
plans to use 200 million US dollars of foreign funds to support
local agricultural development this year.
</P>
<P>
According to a plan set by the provincial agricultural
department, the province will adopt all possible measures to
attract foreign investment in farming, animal breeding and the
improvement of farming facilities.
</P>
<P>
The province's 35 counties neighboring Beijing and Tianjin
municipalities will take their geographic advantages to woo
foreign investment to develop vegetable production. In each of the
counties, at least one foreign-funded agricultural firm will be
set up within this year.
</P>
<P>
To fulfill this, the province will organize agricultural
departments at various levels to actively attend trade fairs and
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the province will try to obtain loans from
international financial organizations and foreign governments to
improve its agricultural production conditions.
</P>
<P>
Only 71 million US dollars of foreign funds were used for the
agricultural sector in the province last year. 
</P>
