<HEADLINE> Vik Takes Final Event, Lajunen Wins Season Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Bjarte Engen Vik of Norway won the
final event by skiing to his third straight World Cup Nordic
Combined victory on Sunday in Strbska Pleso, Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
However, the season title still went to Samppa Lajunne of
Finland who finished fourth on Sunday, 1:24.6 behind Vik.
</P>
<P>
From a 78-second deficit, Vik skied the fastest to clinch the
final event of the season by finishing the cross country run in 37
minutes 48.2 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Vik, fifth after the ski jumping, beat Japan's Kenji Ogiwara by
30.3 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Ogiwara, who was tied for third after the jumping with Czech
Jan Matura, started the race three seconds ahead of Vik.
</P>
<P>
Jari Mantila of Finland who set off the 15-km cross country
race first with a margin of 33 seconds ahead of countryman
Lajunen, was the only finisher in the top 10 who took longer than
40 minutes to complete the course (40:21.7) and finished third,
1:18.5 behind Vik.
</P>
<P>
Mantila still finished second in the overall standings, ending
50 points ahead of Vik. 
</P>
