<HEADLINE> Shanghai Retail Market Brisk </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 24 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shanghai
Municipality registered a total retail volume of 11.03 billion
yuan in February, up 4.1 percent over the same period last year in
real terms.
</P>
<P>
The increased figure was consiered largely due to brisk sales
during China's traditional Spring Festival season which started on
February 7, when shops launched a series of sales promoting
activities, thus resulting in an extended period of consumption.
</P>
<P>
According to government statistics, household electronic
appliances and gold jewelry were the "hottest items" on the market.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the sales volume of color TV sets in 16
large stores in the city increased by 30 percent over the same
period of last year and that of VCD players rose by tenfold.
</P>
<P>
The business volume in the suburban areas of the city increased
by a large margin, too, according to government sources. 
</P>
