An official of the Qinhuangdao development zone said that 1996
saw an increase in the number and scale of overseas investment
projects, with 61 projects approved.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investors came from twelve countries and regions, but
mostly from the Republic of Korea, the United States and Hong
Kong, with the projects covering a wide range of industries and
sectors.
</P>
<P>
Of the newly approved projects, 14 had an investment of over
ten million US dollars each, accounting for 87 percent of the
total figure.
</P>
<P>
About 60 percent of the investments were actually used last
year, while four of the newly approved project became operational
within the year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
