<HEADLINE> Mortar Blast Kills 4 Children in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 24 (Xinhua) -- At least four children died and
one was injured after a mortar shell they were playing with
exploded in the small central Java town of Kebumen on Sunday,
Antara news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The four children, aged between two and fourteen, instantly
died at the site of explosion, while another one, who is currently
being hospitalized, sustained serious injury, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The children apparently picked up the mortar at the nearby
Brencong beach, which is frequently used for military exercises.
</P>
<P>
The Kebumen police chief, Lieutenant Colonel Nuryanto Suharto,
said there is no need to find a "scapegoat" for the incident, as
it was "purely an accident", and all parties should simply accept
what has happened.  
