<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade Active In Fangchenggang City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, March 24 (Xinhua) -- Fangchenggang, a port city in
southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, has made
remarkable progress in foreign trade since the beginning of this
year.
</P>
<P>
During the first two months this year, the city has achieved
18.79 million US dollars in import and export trade, or a 5.62
percent increase over the same period of 1996. The figures does
not include border trade.
</P>
<P>
Of that, total export volume was 14.61 million US dollars, with
an increase of 22.2 percent, leaving a favorable balance of 10.43
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The development of Fangchenggang, which borders Vietnam, is
considered an important part of the construction of the passage
out to the sea in southwest China. 
</P>
