seconds for the 6.7-kilometer course, ahead of Britain's Veerle
Radcliffe and Ethiopia's Getenesh Wami.
</P>
<P>
The race, held in urban Turin's Parco Valentino, cost the
international athletics federation a cool 1.3 million US dollars
in 4,000 cubic meters of fresh turf laid down to spruce up the
city park to international cross country standards.
</P>
<P>
The turf will be removed next week, IAAF officials said.
