<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OIC Summit Condemns Israel's Expansionist Policies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 24 (Xinhua) -- The special summit of the
Organization of Islamic Conference has strongly condemned Israel's
expansionist policies and urged the member states to review
relations with it.
</P>
<P>
The OIC member states should make their relations contingent
"on the extent to which Israel complies with UN resolutions and
with the agreements, commitments and obligations reached by the
parties concerned for the peace process," said a declaration
adopted at the end of the summit in Islamabad on Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
The declaration called on the international community to compel
Israel to fully implement all the agreements concluded in the
framework of the peace process in accordance with their timetable.
</P>
<P>
It also affirmed its support of the Middle East peace process
and implementation of all agreements signed within its framework
between the concerned parties.
</P>
<P>
The declaration also called on the United Nations to take
necessary measures to compel Israel to immediately halt its
confiscation of Palestinian territory and the construction of new
settlements.
</P>
<P>
The OIC states pledged to continue to support the position of
the Palestinian Liberation Organization and the National Authority
in the negotiations aimed at realizing total Israeli withdrawal
from the Palestinian territories occupied in 1967, it said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970324.0213 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-24 </DATE_TIME>
