<HEADLINE> UN/OAU Envoy Arrives for Lome Summit on Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOME, March 23 (Xinhua) -- Joint special envoy of the United
Nations and the Organization of African Unity (OAU) Mohamed
Sahnoun arrived here today for the Wednesday OAU summit on the
Zairean conflict.
</P>
<P>
The Lome summit will focus on setting up a mechanism for the
implementation of a U.N./OAU five-point peace plan in Zaire which
demands an immediate cease-fire and negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Before his arrival, Sahnoun had visited Zaire and met rebel
leader Laurent Kabila and the Zairean government officials.
</P>
<P>
The Zairean government has agreed to a truce, but it was
reported that Kabila told Sahnoun on Saturday that he won't quit
fighting until he defeats Zairean President Mobutu Sese Seko.
</P>
<P>
An ambassador-level meeting will be convened here on Monday to
prepare for the summit and a ministerial-level meeting on its
eve, a local radio report said today.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Minister of Gabon arrived at Lome, the capital of
Togo, today.
</P>
<P>
An OAU delegation led by OAU Secretary-General Salim Ahmed
Salim arrived here on Saturday for the summit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
